{
  "stem": "19969.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "The special session was called in September of 1993, six months after my grandson was killed, and the legislature adopted a-- rather one of the toughest measures in the United States on juveniles and handguns.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But our organization, PUNCH, we raised about $50,000 and put on a campaign, a statewide campaign, to influence legislators to enact that legislation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "My wife and I put in about half of that, about-- about $25,000-- that we spent on that effort and we're continuing that effort today as far as juveniles and handguns are concerned.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We are, of course, always opposed by the National Rifle Association, who believes that everybody should be free to kill everybody, as far as I can understand their philosophy.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But despite that it's a very formidable organization and has a good many million dollars year in revenues, we were able here in Colorado to adopt a rather strict law.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And since that time, over 200 kids have been picked up and charged with carrying handguns, very often in the schools.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "So we're making some headway, but the way society is today who knows.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Money talks big and the gun industry is a billion dollar a year industry.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "The people making money from that source don't like to have any impediment put in the way of their selling guns-- to who, they don't care as long as they can sell guns.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Well, it took a lot of our energy away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "We have not-- and a lot of our money and time-- and we have not traveled hardly any since that day.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "We do no more overseas travel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "All we do is we get together with our annual reunion every year.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "I arrange for that and conduct it.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
